main event: Two bright silvery objects were observed in the sky for several hours in Del Paso Heights, California on July 19, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were described as round, the size of a half dollar, and had an upper and lower part.
The objects were reported to make a humming sound.
The observer watched the objects straight and out of sight over the course of 3-4 hours.
The weather conditions were clear with good visibility.
The Air Force concluded the objects were likely the morning star (Jupiter) and associated planets.
sighted object: Two bright silvery round objects with upper and lower parts
